President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Bruce Hamilton as a member of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board. Hamilton is currently a consultant to the nuclear industry and previously served as President of Fuelco LLC. He also has experience as the Director of Luminant Power at Comanche Peak NPP and as a Captain in the U.S. Navy. Hamilton holds a B.S. from Texas A&M University, an M.A. from the Naval Postgraduate School, and a Ph.D. from The Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy at Tufts University.